Event reconstruction and characterization starts from calibrated cell data that are grouped into collections based on their proximity in both space and time~\cite{ref:DBSCAN,ref:Baird}.  The cell data in each collection is assumed to arise from the same primary neutrino or cosmic-ray event.  The 
cell energy depositions in these events are then used to reconstruct charged particle trajectories.  In this analysis the reconstruction of muon tracks produced in {\ensuremath{\nu_{\mu}}\xspace}~CC interactions is performed using an algorithm based on the Kalman filter technique~\cite{nickdpf,Kalman}.



